VideoGrace videoconferencing system client application
~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~

Installation is performed in the user's home directory 
/home/user/.vgclient/ sudo is not required

Installation
~~~~~~~~~~~~

1. Execute: ./install.sh
2. Run ~/.vgclient/VideoGraceClient from the terminal 
or using the icon on your desktop. The first time you run the icon 
allow the program to run.


If the program does not start, you need to get the two libraries:

On debian-embedded systems:

sudo apt install libxcb-cursor0
sudo apt install libxcb-ewmh2

On rpm-like systems:

sudo yum install xcb-util-cursor 
sudo yum install xcb-util-wm

The update is done automatically from the server

Uninstall
~~~~~~~~~

1. Run sudo ./uninstall.sh and/or rm -rf ~/.vgclient/

